                <a href="/news/dr-hopcrofts-research-was-featured-scientific-american">
                 <h3>
                  Dr. Hopcroft's research was featured in Scientific American
                 </h3>
                </a>
                Scientific American, the longest continuously published magazine in the U.S., has been bringing its readers unique insights about developments in science and technology for more than 170 years. Dr. Rosemary Hopcroft is now forever a piece of this global enterprise. Hopcroft's research backs up study author Shige Song examinations in the article "Wealthy Families Invest More in Sons".
                <strong>
                 <a href="/news/dr-hopcrofts-research-was-featured-scientific-american">
                  <span class="read-more">
                   Dr. Hopcroft's research was featured in Scientific American
                  </span>
