             <section class="block block-views" id="block-views-faculty-spotlight-block">
              <h2 class="block-title">
               Study Abroad
              </h2>
              <div class="view view-faculty-spotlight view-id-faculty_spotlight view-display-id-block view-dom-id-ff047f9629bca4f5dce2fe6af43f0aac">
               <div class="view-content">
                <div class="views-row views-row-1 views-row-odd views-row-first views-row-last">
                 <div class="views-field views-field-field-directory-photo">
                  <div class="field-content">
                   <img alt="" height="115" src="https://sociology.uncc.edu/sites/sociology.uncc.edu/files/styles/directory-thumbnail/public/fields/faculty-spotlight/photo/cuba.jpg?itok=7qZm4o4b" width="115"/>
                  </div>
                 </div>
                 <div class="views-field views-field-title">
                  <span class="field-content">
                   <a href="/faculty-spotlight/cuba-race-identity-and-culture">
                    Cuba: Race, Identity and Culture
                   </a>
                  </span>
                 </div>
                 <div class="views-field views-field-body">
                  <div class="field-content">
                   <p>
                    This 14-day journey will examine Cuba’s history and culture and explore how African cultures blended with European influences to create contemporary Cuban culture. Through cultural immersion, guided tours, and excursions, students will have music, dance, art, and religious encounters that allow them to examine their lives in the U.S. in relation to the values, norms, and cultural experiences of Cubans. Application deadline is February 1, 2019.
                   </p>
                   <p>
                    <a data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://studyabroad.uncc.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction%3DPrograms.ViewProgramAngular%26id%3D11635&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1537974103230000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHT337hyWxZ43nqmeZxYpxScyXuhQ" href="https://studyabroad.uncc.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Programs.ViewProgramAngular&amp;id=11635" target="_blank">
                     Cuba Study Abroad Information Link
                    </a>
                   </p>
                  </div>
                 </div>
                 <div class="views-field views-field-edit-node">
                  <span class="field-content">
                  </span>
                 </div>
                </div>
               </div>
              </div>
             </section>
             <!-- /.block -->
             <section class="block block-views" id="block-views-alumni-spotlight-block">
              <h2 class="block-title">
               Alumni Spotlight
              </h2>
              <div class="view view-alumni-spotlight view-id-alumni_spotlight view-display-id-block view-dom-id-cfc213fab2ba1df92447826294cc0f4d">
               <div class="view-content">
                <div class="views-row views-row-1 views-row-odd views-row-first views-row-last">
                 <div class="views-field views-field-field-directory-photo">
                  <div class="field-content">
                   <img alt="" height="115" src="https://sociology.uncc.edu/sites/sociology.uncc.edu/files/styles/directory-thumbnail/public/fields/alumni-spotlight/photo/Ron_DeJoseph.jpg?itok=5olFGX9c" width="115"/>
                  </div>
                 </div>
                 <div class="views-field views-field-title">
                  <span class="field-content">
                   <a href="/alumni-spotlight/ron-dejoseph">
                    Ron DeJoseph
                   </a>
                  </span>
                 </div>
                 <div class="views-field views-field-body">
                  <div class="field-content">
                   <p>
                    <!--break-->
                    <strong>
                     Ron DeJoseph
                    </strong>
                    graduated from UNC Charlotte in 1994 with a Bachelors in Sociology. After completing his degree, Mr. DeJoseph attained a certificate in broadcasting from the Carolina School of Broadcasting.  These experiences provided Mr. DeJoseph the foundation to pursue an outstanding career working for companies like ESPN and Cox Media Group.
                    <!--break-->
                    Mr. DeJoseph is currently the Promotions Manager with WSOC-TV, where he has won 10 Midsouth Emmys for his work in broadcasting.  Mr. DeJoseph’s job is research driven, and he notes that his Sociology Degree offered him an understanding of research that helped him feel comfortable when he began working in an environment where market research is widely used to understand people and their viewing habits.
                   </p>
                   <p>
                    His advice to current sociology majors: “
                    <em>
                     Try everything you can in terms of your career.  It’s not easy when you are 21 years old to know what you want to do with your life.  If you work hard, opportunities pop up when you least expect them.
                    </em>
                    ” - Ron DeJoseph
                   </p>
                  </div>
                 </div>
                 <div class="views-field views-field-edit-node">
                  <span class="field-content">
                  </span>
                 </div>
                </div>
               </div>
              </div>
             </section>
